tip.text: Their signature Matcha lava cake is a must to order. They also have a wide selection of food and dessert. Will be back to try out the rest.
Come for the for cozy ambience and the croissants with coffee
Love the mango charlotte and earl grey opera cake!
Most of the food is good. Would recommend the kraffmen baked egg. As for the side dish, try the potato rosti (can be slightly dry, but the taste is good, also try the peanut butter Nutella milkshake
Love the Matcha lava cake, however it can be a little sweet, will be back for the choc lava cake soon, buttermilk pancakes are good, but it can be slightly dry, still worth the try.
Try the blue chrysanthemum and earl grey lavender. Don't miss out on salted peanut butter as well
The Pho is a must. Also try out the pomelo salad.
The Angus Beef Tenderloin is the best! Don't forget the crepe Suzette and lemon tart.

Peaceful and good for a weekend getaway. Rooms are nice and clean and there is a natural stream nearby for a walk among nature
